{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-24T06:41:24Z", "url": "https://www.globalresearch.ca/selected-articles-economic-prosperity-neutrality-peace/5885253", "publishedAt": "2025-04-24T06:41:24Z", "content": "Economic Prosperity Neutrality and Peace. Peter Koenig\r\nBy Peter Koenig, April 23, 2025\r\nPeace is an economic driver for every country, for the world and even more so in a globalized world, where cou… [+2641 chars]", "title": "Selected Articles: Economic Prosperity – Neutrality and Peace", "fullContent": "Economic Prosperity – Neutrality and Peace. Peter Koenig\n\nBy Peter Koenig, April 23, 2025\n\nPeace is an economic driver for every country, for the world and even more so in a globalized world, where countries and regions are connected. Conflicts and wars interrupt not only supply chains, harming also economies that have nothing directly to do with the conflict, but they destroy countries physically and economically.\n\nTrump Tariffs: A Sudden Sledgehammer to Crack a Long Term Nut\n\nBy Rodney Atkinson, April 23, 2025\n\nDonald Trump has applied a blizzard of trade tariffs across most industrial sectors and countries, rowing back, reducing, delaying and re-applying tariffs which are applied not so much as where other countries have prejudiced US goods but also where countries simply have a balance of payments surplus with the USA – or, in the case of the UK, even a deficit!\n\nSugary Drinks Linked to More Than 330,000 Deaths a Year\n\nBy Dr. Joseph Mercola, April 23, 2025\n\nYou grab a soda or energy drink without a second thought, but those tasty sips are hiding a big health bill. Most of these drinks are sweetened with refined fructose — typically in the form of high-fructose corn syrup (HFCS) — which causes serious long-term health damage.\n\nIsrael Stalls and the International Court of Justice Complies\n\nBy Rick Sterling, April 23, 2025\n\nOne year ago, the International Court of Justice ruled that Israel had 15 months to prepare their defense (“counter memorial”) against the charges of genocide filed by South Africa. They were told to present their arguments by 28 July 2025.\n\nDeclassified: Biden Regime ‘Countering Domestic Terrorism’ Playbook\n\nBy Ben Bartee, April 23, 2025\n\nWith the “worst attack on American soil since Pearl Harbor,” January 6th, as the pretext, the Biden regime in 2021 devised its Orwellian “Strategic Implementation Plan For Countering Domestic Terrorism,” recently declassified by DNI chief Tulsi Gabbard.\n\nAustralia’s Growing Role in US Nuclear Strategy in Asia-Pacific. US-Australia Strategic Focus Against China?\n\nBy Drago Bosnic, April 23, 2025\n\nIt’s no secret that the United States is shifting strategic focus to China. This process has been going on for decades, but is catching pace in recent times. It should be noted that both the troubled Biden and the new Trump administrations have been quite consistent in this regard, despite perceived differences in their approach to Russia and internal policies.\n\nChina’s Tariff Smackdown. Interview with Hua Bin\n\nBy Hua Bin and Mike Whitney, April 23, 2025\n\nTrump may think he is playing 3D chess, but his plan has not been well-thought out, which is obvious now that China has refused to back down. After stocks, bonds and the Dollar went into free fall, he panicked and rolled back part of his program, which is a clear sign of poor preparation and faulty assumptions."}
